FirstRand Bank Hires Five for First Asian Syndicated Loan

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-22T10:12:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/firstrand-said-to-seek-2-year-100-million-loan-from-group-of-asian-banks.html
FirstRand Bank Ltd., a unit of  South
Africa â€™s second-largest financial services group, hired five
banks for its first Asian syndicated loan.  China Construction Bank Corp., Bank of Taiwan, Bank of
Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd., ChinaTrust Commercial Bank and the
Export-Import Bank of the Republic of  China  are arranging a $100
million, two-year facility, FirstRand said in an e-mailed
response to questions from Bloomberg today.  The loan will pay interest of 1.35 percentage point more
than the London Interbank Offered Rate, the statement said.
Those committing at least $10 million will get 1.85 percentage
point in interest and fee payments, and those lending at least
$5 million will get 1.8 percentage point.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
